                "institute": "1USAMSU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed using coupled",
                "cyclotrons at the National Superconducting Cyclotron",
                "Laboratory"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fragments produced and emitted at very",
                "forward angles were transmitted and separated and",
                "momentum analyzed based on their mass-to-charge",
                "ratio using the A1900 fragment separator. The",
                "fragments were selected and transmitted through the",
                "separator by varying the magnetic rigidity of the",
                "whole device from 3.628 to 5.228 Tm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Five 5 x 5 cm2 Si p-type intrinsic",
                "n-type detectors with thicknesses of 980, 966,",
                "1001, 988, and 992 mu-m, and a 10-cm thick plastic",
                "scintillator with an active area of 15 x 10 cm2, both",
                "located at the focal plane approx. 35 m downstream",
                "from the target, were used to measure the energy",
                "losses and kinetic energies of the fragments in order",
                "to identify each transmitted particle.The 966 mu-m",
                "thick Si detector and the thick plastic scintillator",
                "were also used to provide start signals for the time",
                "of flight (TOF) relative to the cyclotron's rf for 35-",
                "m path length from the target to the focal plane"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A pair of parallel plate avalanche counters",
                "located in the focal-plane position was used",
                "to track the ions and to correct for different path",
                "lengths traveled by the particles."
              ]
            }
          ],
